9yDpE66_VXm9qA_c06qtTnVvxNp8TeKUdmBeF_OL2fCqfO0gPR3KQM8SXWNFQTqnAokc1zYRK0P=
8H_QGZ-IFE], so I=E2=80=99m on high-alert. If the real thing turns out to b=
e anything like the books=E2=80=99 fictional OASIS, the decisions that the =
platform owner makes will have an unprecedented impact on billions of lives=
=2E=C2=A0
Ready Player One takes place in a VR world powered by an advanced Oculus Qu=
est-like headset. Ready Player Two raises the stakes when it moves players =
from VR headsets to ONI, a non-invasive neural interface through which play=
ers can control their avatars and experience others=E2=80=99 lives just by =
thinking. Facebook has its own answer to ONI in CTRL-labs, which brings gre=
at promise and great danger, and will need to be regulated appropriately if=
 it comes to market.
Dystopian visions aside, in both fiction and, I suspect, reality, the compa=
ny that owns the Metaverse will be the most valuable in the world. We=E2=80=
=99re many years away, and I prefer Tencent and Epic=E2=80=99s more decentr=
alized approach [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkEtuhTAMRVfzMivKh_AZZ=
NBJt4ECNrwISFDitKKrbx5IrSrZsuQr--jeyRIuIZ7mCIlYThgHB0Y0slO67hmYGkSnO-bSMEfE=
3brNUMzIjjxubrLkgr8uOJeaPY3Seh7nWdetaETbgwLeN3rWvAVbyxbYizPYDA79hAY_MZ7BI9v=
Mk-hID_X-kB-lfKAxROeXKuUxkZ3Wagp7EY7S9Lr1lN4got0Tc0ZyyYUUtVC6UX0lKpnd_L0qGB=
08ar4v8t8fFs0voMjr0-64XUKxNZS5Z-_oHNDbcUO4HdOd0WWAzgONx6-0IRHGe1likFrKhjctK=
zQIJS3_B_oBcul85g], but Facebook is a contender, and you get that upside po=
tential for free.=C2=A0
Putting it All Together
Facebook is hard to love. Concerns around privacy and anticompetitive behav=
ior abound, it rips off other companies=E2=80=99 product work, and I=E2=80=
=99m not convinced Mark Zuckerberg isn=E2=80=99t a robot.=C2=A0
But as Ben Graham told a young Warren Buffett, =E2=80=9CIn the short run, t=
he stock market is a voting machine; in the long run, it=E2=80=99s a weighi=
ng machine.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
Facebook will do more than $80 billion in revenue with gross margins over 8=
0% and EBITDA margins over 40%. Half of the people in the world outside of =
China use its products. It=E2=80=99s built arguably the best business model=
 in the world. It stands to benefit as much as anyone this side of Seattle =
from the dramatic and sudden shift to eCommerce.
But despite that, it=E2=80=99s trading at the lowest P/E multiple among FAA=
MG, eCommerce, and social media companies.=C2=A0
There are obvious headwinds. We=E2=80=99ve discussed many in the piece, inc=
luding an active antitrust lawsuit, and we haven=E2=80=99t even mentioned t=
wo of the strongest:=C2=A0=C2=A0
Apple=E2=80=99s IDFA update [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUEmOhDAMf=
E3nBsrKwCGHvsw3UBaniRoSlGUQ8_oJ9GEkS2VVyS67jCrwiumUe8wF1Qxp9laSgY5M8AlZyS0Z=
xYh8nl0C2JRfZUkV0F716o0qPoZ7AmMq0CJHjs0k6MDE4IwSANRObLAMuMOOWoYun1lV6yEYkPA=
D6YwB0CqXUvb8YM8H_W51HEfvlAEd47s3cWuUrtkHyLm1AY4L9gS7Sj68ulhT19oSIOXOxdT5mD=
